
Visual Model

Assumes every element generates 1 or more element boxes
Element Box:
    content area surrounded by optional padding, borders, outlines, margins

Box properties & types:
    Normal flow
        text renders left to right, tp to bottom
    Block
        gen by p, div, headings
        stack vertically, 'new line'
        any el can be made to gen with 'display:block'
    Replaced element
        completely replaced by content, e.g img
    Inline
        e.g. strong, em elments
        no 'new line'
        any el can be made to gen with 'display:inline'

Backgrounds 
    applied within padding by default
    visible through gaps in border style
    parent's always visible thr. margins


Margins 
    can have negative lengths

Borders
    Styles: sold, inset
    border-color property
        if not set, is foreground color of content

Link to stylesheet file
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css" type="text/css">
    
Selectors
    <name> Element name
	.<name>	class
	#<name>	id
    [class*="blah-"]    class name starts with 'blah-'


Colours
	tomato

Fonts
    indicate size with rem unit.


